tscan
------------------------------------------
T-Scan is an analysis tool for dutch texts to assess the complexity of the
text, and is based on original work by Rogier Kraf (Utrecht University) (see:
Kraf et al., 2009). The code has been reimplemented and extended by Ko van der
Sloot (Tilburg University), and is currently maintained and continued by
Martijn van der Klis (Utrecht University).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libfolia17-2.10-1bl2
  libfrog3-0.24-1bl2
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libgomp1-11.3.0-1
  libicu70-70.1-1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  libticcutils9-0.28-1bl2
  libtimbl6-6.6-1bl2
  libxml2-2.9.12-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.38-1
  cygport-0.35.1-1
  flex-2.6.4-2
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  libfolia-devel-2.10-1bl2
  libfrog-devel-0.24-1bl2
  libicu-devel-70.1-1
  libticcutils-devel-0.28-1bl2
  libtimbl-devel-6.6-1bl2
  libtool-2.4.7-1
  libxml2-devel-2.9.12-2
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/proycon/tscan

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/proycon/tscan/archive/refs/tags/v0.9.8.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack tscan-0.9.8-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./tscan-0.9.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/tscan-0.9.8-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/tscan-0.9.8-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

